data.text:
Sir Guildford "Guilford" Dudley

Born 1535 in Northumberland, England

Ancestors

Husband of Jane (Grey) Dudley — married 25 May 1553 in Durham House, London, England

Died 12 Feb 1554 at about age 19 in Tower Green, Tower of London, London, England

Profile last modified 21 Jun 2024 | Created 9 Feb 2013

This page has been accessed 4,651 times.

Biography

Guilford was the son of John Dudley, Duke of Northumberland. Power-hungry and eager to sustain the cause of the Protestants, his father locked him into an unlucky marriage with Jane Grey, the nine days queen. Mary I imprisoned the young couple in the Tower and had them beheaded on the same day [1]. Northumberland was arrested and beheaded after his army was defeated. [2]

Ironically, Guilford's brother, Robert Dudley, Earl of Leicester became Queen Elizabeth I's favourite.[2]
